      <abstract>
        <p>Readers respond to Marshall Sella's May 21 article on reality-based television shows; photo (S) /// 55 NYT 06 18 00 0006 00008 4 84 I 735280 LETTERS***Readers respond to Marshall Sella's May 21 article on reality-based television shows (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Marshall Sella's report on reality-based TV programs piqued readers' curiosity about the viewers -- some say voyeurs -- to whom these shows will appeal. Others, pointing to our articles on Africa, said that these ''candid cameras'' might be employed more usefully to expose suffering.</p>
      </block>
